      @Test void testAddFlow()
      Tests the addFlow method in the WorkLoad.java class. The test adds new flows to "Example4.txt" or whichever test file you choose. It compares the actual values and expected values by iterating through both using a for loop.

    • testAddFlowJustNumbers

      @Test void testAddFlowJustNumbers()
      Tests the addFlow method in the WorkLoad.java class. The test adds new flows of just numbers to "Example4.txt" or whichever test file you choose. It compares the actual values and expected values by iterating through both using a for loop.

    • testAddNodeToFlow

      @Test void testAddNodeToFlow()

      @Test void testAddNodeToFlowAddingToNewFlow()

    • testGetTotalTxAttemptsInFlow

    • testGetFlowPriority

      @Test void testGetFlowPriority()
      Test the GetFlowPriority method in WorkLoad.java. First gets a list of the nodes in priority order, then iterates through both the actual list and expected comparing the values.

    • testSetFlowPriority

      @Test void testSetFlowPriority()
      Tests the setFlowPriority method in WorkLoad.java. Takes the flows in priority order then puts the priorities in descending order (first flow having the priority of the last and vice versa), checking to make sure it is successfully changed.

    • testGetFlowTxAttemptsPerLink

      @Test void testGetFlowTxAttemptsPerLink()
      Tests getFlowTxAttemptsPerLink method from the WorkLoad.java file. Adds a flow to the workload, gets the flow names, and compares the No. of transmission attempts per link to the expected output.

    • testSetFlowsInRMOrder

      @Test void testSetFlowsInRMOrder()
      Tests the setFlowsInRMorder method in the WorkLoad.java class. Test first calls the method then compares the output with the expected values.

    • testSetFlowsInRMOrderChangePriorityandPeriod

      @Test void testSetFlowsInRMOrderChangePriorityandPeriod()
      Tests the setFlowsInRMorder method in the WorkLoad.java class. Test first changes the period and priority of the second flow "F1" to make sure it appears before "F0".

    • testGetNodeNamesInAlphabeticalOrder

      @Test void testGetNodeNamesInAlphabeticalOrder()
      Tests getNodeNamesOrderedAlphabetically method in WorkLoad.java class. Takes the names of all the nodes in the Example4.txt file and orders them alphabetically, taking account if they are integers.
